- Always use the latest version of rust packages.
- Always ensure test coverage is above 90%.
- For rust the backend framework used is axum.
- Make code modular and extendable following all good design priciples.
- Lint the code properly using rust-analyzer.
- Create folders for modules if needed. Always arrange code properly.
- Always use sea-orm for orm and queries.
- I am making data visualization / query backend.
- Use @tanstack/react-query for data fetching at client side in the frontend.
- Use tailwind css, and react functions and eslint.
- Use radix-ui wherever possible for components instead of creating from scratch.
- Use google's material-symbols for icons.
- Do not add comments when generating code.
